==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cockateel
<hw>Cock"a*teel</hw></mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small gray and white Australian
parrot (<spn>Leptolophus hollandicus</spn>, formerly <spn>Calopsitta
Nov⟦ae⟧-Hollandi⟦ae⟧</spn>) with a prominent crest; the male has bright
yellow cheeks and crest, but the female has only a pale yellow in the
face; -- it is so called from its note.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cockateel, cockatoo parrot, <spn>Nymphicus
hollandicus</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cockatoo</ent>⟦br⟧
